Description: Rim and body sherd of East Greek pottery eye cup; interior glazed with one added red band lined in white; exterior: part of large eye and arching eyebrow with horizontal band below the decorated field.
Curator's comments: From the same vessel as GR1886.4-1.1038.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 256, no. 6)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.465)
